feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1641.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Death of EQ's Casual-Raid Playerbase</span><hr size=1> The problems you bring up are so much as a problem on our server as they are on others.  Come 5pm PST there are still a good number of &quot;bosses&quot; up between Velious and Luclin on Lanys.  Also we don't seem to have as strong euro/asian guilds here as on other servers.  There was actually a very good rant about this on Lagacy of Steel's webpage, it might still be there. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.net">www.legacyofsteel.net</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
One solution are randomizing spawn times.  This can be very frustrating on two fronts, 1 is for those who have a rotation, the other is for raids/guilds who need a large amount of time to plan something.  Right now, due to the amount of emerging 'casual gamers' along with SoL abilities and spells, there are a good number of boss mobs that can be taken down with the right leader.  Doze, CT, Vindi, Statue, Rhags could all probably be taken out by open raids.  The problem is that these open raids require a week or two to plan.  If the spawn timer in random, it's very difficult for the casual gamer to perhaps get a chance at one of these.  Yes, these are all pretty much dead on a patch day, but if you plan a raid for let's say 2 weeks after a patch, you have a fairly good shot at having the forces avalible and ready to get the mob.  I think randomizing spawn times would only hurt the casual gamer, and frustrate the power gamers.<br>
<br>
Another option, would be to increase spawn times.  As EQ ages and more players come into the &quot;end game&quot; another way to give everyone a chance at the mobs would to be to have them spawn more often.  The flip side to this is, if boss mobs spawn more often, loot enters the server more often, a lot of the aura of having it is lost.<br>
<br>
A third option is more content.  There is still a bunch of content in SoL that has yet to be unlocked.  Depending on the fights/rewards, you might find uber guilds pretty much leaving Velious all together as more of it's unlocked.  But right now since a lot of it is still a.)being discoverd b.)bugged or c.)not implemented yet, the content we do have avalible is becoming more crowded.  Perhaps we need another Velious type expansion next. <p><center><img src="http://merkabaeq.homestead.com/files/merky.jpg"><br>
