 <p><center><img src="http://theregulators.securedata.net/gpics/Psych Sig CALKA.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uerrtai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Errtai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/4/02 7:17:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1641.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Death of EQ's Casual-Raid Playerbase</span><hr size=1> I really like this post a lot.  There is a pretty steep learning curve for up and coming guilds in EQ.  They start out being able to put plane of hate/fear on the calendar, then even Venril Sathir or Trakanon.  Once they are ready to start farming TOV for armor, they again look to the calendar and get upset when people tell them their days of reserving things to do are pretty much over.  Lanys turns into the wild wild west pretty much after you're done with the planes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Doze, CT, Vindi, Statue, Rhags could all probably be taken out by open raids.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
To get off topic here a bit... Merkaba are you insane? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I think of this list MAYBE the first Rhag could be taken down by an open raid.  I think you have been casting complete heal after someone all night a little too long to realize exactly what an open raid is capable of.  I invite you to plan an open raid on Vindi or Dozer to prove me wrong.  Hell, Vindi is up every single day, if you plan him on a day without Statue I'm sure you could get cooporation to get an open raid in there for a few tries, see what happens.  Everyone knows what to do, you take a warrior, give him a good amont of time to fight by himself before others engage, and cast the CH's in order.  What could go wrong?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uruanolikm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ruanolik M</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/4/02 7:18:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1641.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Death of EQ's Casual-Raid Playerbase</span><hr size=1> I think there's a good point here, but unfortunately because the population now is so cluttered with 50+ people that any solution to the problem, causes more confusion.  This comes to light very easily when you use last week as an example.<br>
<br>
Last week there was no patch.  Anyone notice?<br>
<br>
I personally had to cancel a planar raid, because a mob was up, and an unnamed guild said they couldn't wouldn't wait for my guild to finish.  I knew what was happening.  Other guilds who will also remain nameless, but have a much more common reputation for doing it, had done it to us before.    Rather than have X guild run me over, and flex its muscles, I avoided the pain of a CR, and more complaints and name calling, and bowed down.  <br>
<br>
Apparently, respect is something Lanys doesn't have.  Guilds helping each other?  Not a chance, the big guilds have the maturity of a 10 year old when it comes to their spawns if you are in their way.  They have fine people, but if X mob is up, it's their god given right.  <br>
<br>
There's always a bigger fish.  Its a stupid line but its true.  If Visions leaves NToV FL will compete with ROTA over it.  Where one guild was the casual gamers, they quickly realize that they MUST have loot.  They deserve it, and they will do it.  You can argue they are more organized.  That they have better people.  And they do in some ways, if you can get the loot being an asshole, you can be better equipped, thats Real Life too.  It's the American way.<br>
<br>
It's a game.  You want to be an ass to others and that's what floats your boat fine.  You want to help others, group and have fun?  Do it.  The problem is that unfortunately those that fall in the second category will never see the cool stuff, and I'm one of them.  Even tho, I have every confidence that my guild can take down Cazic Thule, I know that until every other ass guild gets their Cazic loot, mine will not.  Because we aren't the ones who will walk into Fear and claim it.  It's FFA but we don't ignore the calendar.<br>
<br>
Verant can fix spawn timers.  It can't fix players. <p><center>
